article_id:1531,category_name:Events,title_name:Tartarus's Wrath Has Arrived in The Agito Uprising!,image_path:https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/c041e5b9de604173232cace0825e3640.png,message:<div>Tartarus&#39;s Wrath was added to The Agito Uprising (high-difficulty quests where you&#39;ll face powerful foes from a new organization) at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1598594400"></span>! Clear them to earn materials required to craft 6★ weapons!</div><div><br></div><div>&quot;I will destroy this world of many sins,&quot; the Agito said.</div><div>&quot;In order avenge my fallen king,&quot; the Agito said.</div><div>&quot;Everything I do is for my king, for His Majesty, King Alberius.&quot;</div><div><br></div><div>The vengeful determination in the Agito&#39;s gloomy eyes tells of his uprising against all who took his master from him and lived. The dragon who descended half-clad in steel has a name, and that name is Tartarus.</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/c041e5b9de604173232cace0825e3640.png"></div><div>Tartarus&#39;s Wrath (Shadow), Required Might: 22,000</div><div><br></div><div>■New Agito Series Weapons</div><div>Powerful new 6★ Agito weapons were added under Crafting at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1598594400"></span>. You can use materials obtained by defeating Tartarus to craft light-attuned weapons with skills that switch effects each time you use them.</div><div><br></div><div>You must have first obtained specific weapons before you can craft weapons using materials obtained from Tartarus. The required weapons are the tier II light-attuned 5★ weapons that can be crafted using materials obtained from the Luminous Chimera in Void Battles.</div><div><br></div><div>The weapon that is required differs based on the weapon type for the weapon you wish to craft. You can check the requirements by selecting Materials for the Tartarus weapons on the Craft tab under Crafting.</div><div><br></div><div>・Agito weapons cannot be dismantled.</div><div>・Difficulty levels for Tartarus&#39;s Wrath and tier II and higher enhancements for Agito weapons will be added in the future.</div><div><br></div><div>■Treasure Trade for The Agito Uprising</div><div>The Light Tree facility will be added to the Treasure Trade for The Agito Uprising.</div><div>Obtain the Light Tree to boost the HP and strength of light-attuned adventurers.</div><div>・The exchange limit does not reset.</div><div><br></div><div>Note:</div><div>Players must have completed Chapter 10 / 6-3 (Normal) of the main campaign and any of the Standard difficulty Advanced Dragon Trials to participate.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div><div><br></div>,start_time:1598594400,update_time1597743082